Two people died on Thursday and two others injured in a road accident at Zioni junction in Kibwezi along the Nairobi-Mombasa road. According to Kibwezi deputy commissioner Vitalis Ogur, the dead are a woman aged 40 and her 5-year old son. The 8 am accident involved a truck that was headed to Nairobi and a saloon car. Ogur said the truck lost control after a tyre burst and hit the car. "The two died on the spot and the others among them the driver of the saloon car were injured," said Ogur The injured are admitted to Kibwezi sub-county hospital for treatment. Click here for the latest political news 